  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 55 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 700 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fancy-french-onion-beef-tenderloin-64b69f308c02aa0344141105
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
#oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Strip @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves
from stems; finely chop leaves until you have ¼ tsp (½ tsp for 4). (We sent more;
save the rest for another use!) Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}.
Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{},
chopped rosemary, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread out in a
single layer.

Roast on middle rack for ~{16%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).
(For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.)

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over
medium-high heat. Add onion and @Dried Thyme{1%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4); cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, @water{¼%cup}, @Sugar{1%tsp}, and lemon juice
from lemon. Cook until thickened and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Taste and season
with salt and pepper if desired. Transfer to a medium microwave-safe #bowl{};
tightly cover with #plastic wrap{}. Rinse and wipe out pan.

While onion cooks, in a second medium bowl, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon},
@Creamy Horseradish Sauce{1%ounce}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, and a squeeze of
lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season
generously all over with @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Dried Thyme{½%tsp}, salt,
and pepper. (Be sure to measure the thyme—we sent more!)

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Once potatoes have roasted 16 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss
green beans on opposite side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Return to middle rack and roast until potatoes are golden brown and green beans
are lightly browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes} more. (For 4 servings, leave
potatoes roasting; add green beans to a second baking sheet and roast on top
rack.)

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add beef and
cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest for a few minutes.

If necessary, reheat saucy onion in the #microwave{}, ~{15-20%seconds}.

Toss green beans with as much lemon zest as you like.

Slice beef against the grain.

Divide beef, green beans, and potatoes between plates. Top potatoes with saucy
onion and drizzle beef with as much horseradish cream as you like. Serve with
remaining lemon wedges on the side.